OL,5, Patients who have been waiting more    
OL,6, than 40 weeks for treatment in England 
OL,7, will be offered the option of getting  
OL,8, seen in another part of the country.   
OL,10,FAbout 400,000 will be contacted in the 
OL,11,Fcoming weeks and asked whether they    
OL,12,Fwould be willing to travel and how far.
OL,14,FPatients already have a right to ask   
OL,15,Ffor treatment elsewhere.               
OL,17,FBut NHS England believes that by       
OL,18,Fproactively contacting the longest     
OL,19,Fwaiters they will help unlock some of  
OL,20,Fthe worst bottlenecks in the system.   
